name: GIS Reference Question
desc:
From Terry: I want to make an appointment to meet with you or representative to help guide me through the achieve search for old aerial photography in the Juliaetta, Idaho area. I've looked through the photo positives before and know they go back to about 1940.

The coordinate for the Juliaetta site is:

latitude 46.570845° (decimal degrees) or 46°34'15" (degrees, minutes and seconds)

longitude  -116.711528° (decimal degrees) or -116°42'41" (degrees, minutes and seconds)

‌

- [Google Earth](https://earth.google.com/web/search/46.571033077851524,+-116.71156018650466/@46.57103261,-116.71156027,361.03553116a,1600.92722224d,35y,83.319397h,0t,0r/data=Cj4iJgokCUiusbzAYEdAEaENhERgW0dAGS0_ot7rO13AIbJwFhAxRF3AKhAIARIKMTk4NS0xMi0zMRgBQgIIAToDCgEwSg0I____________ARAA "‌")
  - Only goes back to 1985 (and fidelity is low)
- [ArcGIS World Imagery Wayback](https://livingatlas.arcgis.com/wayback/#active=10&mapCenter=-116.71452%2C46.57113%2C16 "‌")
  - Only goes back to 2014
- Check out physical file storage tomorrow
